org.springframework.cloud.aws.jdbc.datasource

Class DataSourceInformation

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.springframework.cloud.aws.jdbc.datasource.DataSourceInformation

  • public final class DataSourceInformation
extends Object
    Immutable parameter object that holds all information needed by the DataSourceFactory implementation to create a datasource. The attributes inside this class represents the minimal information for the DataSourceFactory to actually create the underlying datasource.

    This parameter object is used to allow a more flexible DataSourceFactory interface

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Agim Emruli

    • Constructor Detail

      • DataSourceInformation

        public DataSourceInformation(DatabaseType databaseType,
                             String hostName,
                             Integer port,
                             String databaseName,
                             String userName,
                             String password)
        Main constructor to create this object. This constructor receives all information to fully construct the object and to allow the implementation to be immutable.
        Parameters:
        databaseType - - The database type used by the datasource to connect to. This information will be typically used to instantiate and use the particular driver class to connect to the database platform.
        hostName - - The fully qualified hostname without any protocol or port information (e.g. myDbServer.domain.com, localhost, 192.168.23.1)
        port - - The port used to connect to the particular database platform (eg. 3306 as a default for mysql)
        databaseName - - The database name used to connect to the database. The meaning is database specific for (e.g for mysql the database name, for oracle the SID id)
        userName - - The username used to connect to the database
        password - - The password used to connect to the database

      • getDatabaseName

        public String getDatabaseName()
        The database name used to connect to the database. The information is databaseType type specific.
        • MySQL - This is the database name to connect to
        • Oracle - This is the system id (SID) to connect to
        • SQLSERVER - This information is not used at all
        Returns:
        - The database name that can be used to connect to the database.

      • getUserName

        public String getUserName()

        Returns:
        - The username never null

      • getPassword

        public String getPassword()
        The password used to connect to the database. The password might be empty but not null.
        Returns:
        - the password - never null
